text:
jane addams (september 6, 1860 – may 21, 1935), known as the "mother" of social work, was a pioneer american settlement activist/reformer, social worker, public philosopher, sociologist, public administrator, protestor, author, and leader in women's suffrage and world peace.
she co-founded, with ellen gates starr, an early settlement house in the united states, chicago's hull house that would later become known as one of the most famous settlement houses in america.
in an era when presidents such as theodore roosevelt and woodrow wilson identified themselves as reformers and social activists, addams was one of the most prominent reformers of the progressive era.
she helped america address and focus on issues that were of concern to mothers, such as the needs of children, local public health, and world peace.
in her essay "utilization of women in city government," jane addams noted the connection between the workings of government and the household, stating that many departments of government, such as sanitation and the schooling of children, could be traced back to traditional women's roles in the private sphere.
thus, these were matters of which women would have more knowledge than men, so women needed the vote to best voice their opinions.
she said that if women were to be responsible for cleaning up their communities and making them better places to live, they needed to be able to vote to do so effectively.
addams became a role model for middle-class women who volunteered to uplift their communities.
she is increasingly being recognized as a member of the american pragmatist school of philosophy, and is known by many as the first woman "public philosopher in the history of the united states".
in 1889 she co-founded hull house, and in 1920 she was a co-founder for the aclu.
in 1931 she became the first american woman to be awarded the nobel peace prize, and is recognized as the founder of the social work profession in the united states.

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
toda a linha metoo é composta por mais de 50 itens: bonecas, bonecos,  chaveiros, sofás, luminárias e pelúcias.

o modelo mais conhecido no brasil é a boneca angela,  recentemente a marca lançou a linha para meninos, o boneco panda metoo. existe também outras linhas como a de coala e também a linha bailarina metoo.

antes do nascimento do bebê, as bonecas metoo são excelentes opções para decorar o cantinho. 🌟objeto de transição/apego

logo após os primeiros meses de vida começa a fase do conhecimento, a exploração dos 5 sentidos e apego à objetos. esse ponto é muito importante para o desenvolvimento do bebê, pois existem diversos estudos que comprovam os benefícios em ter um objeto de transição e de apego, principalmente durante o soninho, pois as bonecas e bonecos metoo doll são excelentes opções como objetos de apego, pois elas são tão fofinhas que também são ótimas opções como naninhas na hora de dormir. 🌟aproximação entre mãe e filha(o)

são diversos os tamanhos das bonecas metoo doll, apesar de possuírem tamanhos diferentes existem opções com o mesmo desenho/modelo. por exemplo, os maiores tamanhos se chamam jimbao, e você pode combinar o mesmo tamanho com a mini metoo. 💙
.
🌟qualidade e garantia

as bonecas metoo são fabricadas na china e importadas para o brasil por uma empresa que detém a exclusividade da marca metoo doll, por isso é importante que você saiba de onde está comprando, sempre questione se o produto acompanha nota fiscal ou é original.
ela possuem o selo do inmetro.

importante: apesar de serem bonecas de pano, elas são fabricadas com tecido totalmente anti alérgico.

www.prizinhasbaby.com 📦
.
#metoo #bonecametoo #bonecametoodoll #bomdia #domingo #soninho #maedemenina

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with ficial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

although it's nothing to joke about if he really got attacked by two men on jan 29th.
according to the chicago police latest updates there are a lot of loop holes in his story and it's looking like he fabricated the story for whatever reason. 
as an african american proud gay woman i sure hope he didnt make this up. this could be a major set back for the lgbtq community (hope i didn't leave an alphabet out). living in a world where so many of us are fighting for our rights and respect. if you remember several years ago i had to fight for my rights to use the bathroom because i got kicked out of a beverly hills hotel bathroom and called an 'it" as i was escorted off of the premises. i wish this treatment to no one and for this we have to make sure that when we fight we are fighting for our truth because we are fighting for all of us. may god be with #jussiesmollett.

didn't mean to offend anyone anyone.
remember i'm gay too.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
"she told her story"' acrylic on canvas.
 amazing fact about #crows (one of many): if one crow has an experience or interaction that is traumatic or dangerous, they will call to all of their crow friends, who come and listen to their story and process it. if it includes information about a dangerous being, they will be able to recognize that being based on the description given. the crows, like all species, have something precious for humans to aspire to. a survivor of any type of abuse should be able to share their story in a way that is comfortable to them if they want to. just to be able to state it out loud, to give voice to the self that had to go though a trauma of that nature, is more than enough reason for a person to receive support when they want to come forth with their story. and yet the additional reasons i always hear people give for sharing their stories are that they don't want the same thing to happen to anyone else, or for anyone else it has happened to, they don't want them to feel alone. this is a beyond selfless, indispensable act from a  survivor that should never be expected of them and yet so many choose to to do so with empathy,  grace, endurance and love. i don't know on what basis anyone with can protest this. the crows certainly  don't.
(ps be nice to the crows, they can and do recognize you. watch a murder of crows on @pbs )
.
.
.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i've never been shameful about my mental illness - as i keep putting in those deep breathes and focus out of my chest before i go to the hospital i wanted to show what this looks like.
-
i don't often cry, the last time would have been three months after my child's father and i separated and i had a completely hysterical breakdown at work. stress is a funny thing in which you can seemingly be able to conquer most of it, until one thing becomes too much and it all crashes down on you.
-
too many times i've been in this exact same position before. all the time i was a teenager i would be in the local hospitals at least once a month having a episode of depression or a panic attack and there was no help. 14 referrals to public mental health services in one year and i didn't see a counsellor until after six years of asking for help from a failed public system - i found a therapist and i pay for it ($113 a session weekly.)
-
now i'm back to this. i'm passionless. my creativity is dead. i feel stupid and worthless. i feel defeated and pointless. i feel like i can't do anything right. i honestly envy my child's mind because despite how overwhelming things can be for him he knows how he feels about them. a lot of the time i can't even determine that much let alone what i am to make of it.
-
here i am again, about to ask for help again from people who are ill-equipped to provide it. about to provide the innermost details my childhood and trauma when they ask me that extremely difficult and irritating question: why?
-
i'd honestly love to know why i can't do anything right. id love to know why anything good in my life i'm out to destroy. id love to know why i deserved this.
-
i was once the little girl who was once eager for approval. then i was burned by trust in people who were supposed to care for me. where that's leaves me now is to be someone i don't like - spiteful, emotional, and broken.
-
hashtags:
#ibelieveyou #mentalillness #mentalhealth #stopabuse #emotionalabuse #survivor #childabuse #consent #metoo #letstalk  #speakout

i have never been shameful about my mental illness - as i keep putting in those deep breathes and focus out of my chest before i go to the hospital i wanted to show what this looks like.
-
i do not often cry, the last time would have been three months after my child's father and i separated and i had a completely hysterical breakdown at work. stress is a funny thing in which you can seemingly be able to conquer most of it, until one thing becomes too much and it all crashes down on you.
-
too many times i have been in this exact same position before. all the time i was a teenager i would be in the local hospitals at least once a month having a episode of depression or a panic attack and there was no help. 14 referrals to public mental health services in one year and i didn't see a counsellor until after six years of asking for help from a failed public system - i found a therapist and i pay for it ($113 a session weekly.)
-
now i am back to this. i am passionless. my creativity is dead. i feel stupid and wohless. i feel defeated and pointless. i feel like i can not do anything right. i honestly envy my child's mind because despite how overwhelming things can be for him he knows how he feels about them. a lot of the time i can not even determine that much let alone what i am to make of it.
-
here i am again, about to ask for help again from people who are ill-equipped to provide it. about to provide the innermost details my childhood and trauma when they ask me that extremely difficult and irritating question: why?
-
i'd honestly love to know why i can not do anything right. id love to know why anything good in my life i am out to destroy. id love to know why i deserved this.
-
i was once the little girl who was once eager for approval. then i was burned by trust in people who were supposed to care for me. where that's leaves me now is to be someone i do not like - spiteful, emotional, and broken.
-

text:
הצלנו חיים. כל כמה זמן אני מקבל הודעה על תלמיד או תלמידה שהצליחו להגן על עצמם. את ההודעה הזאת שקיבלתי ממתאמנת שלנו אני חייב לשתף: "אחרי כמה שניות של מחשבה החלטתי לנסות את התרגיל שתרגלנו בשיעור. הצלחתי להוריד אותו ממני. הוא היה בשוק שהצלחתי להוריד אותו ממני והוא הפסיק לנסות.

מסר שחשוב לי להעביר הלאה זה שעבורי, הקרב מגע לא רק תורם לי פיזית, אלא גם מנטאלית. האימונים הם מסע עבורי, נותן לי תחושת שליטה על הגוף שלי, ושאף אחד לא יכול לגרום לי לעשות משהו שאני לא רוצה. זה נתן לי את הביטחון ללכת בלי הפחד שיתקפו אותי"

text:
@onthebasisofsex @ruuuthbaderginsburg 
#basedontrueevents

i saw this movie a fortnight ago, and its taken me a while to decide how to put into words what i thought about the film.

honestly, i was left so #inspired.
this is the story of ruth bader gunsburg. a strong, resilient, and intelligent woman who is one of those greats that helped to open doors and opportunities for woman that had previously been closed. her fearlessness and courage in a era where men, and society in general, felt the place of the woman was 'in the kitchen' and i find this so admirable. this is film that i feel all woman should watch and will feel a strong connection to.

the movie is just a snapshot of her life, and some of the struggles she had to face in a "mans world", but i feel the film is still able capture ruth's true essence and the core of womans rights that were hard fought via generations of  strong woman like ruth who fought for basic liberties and to be taken seriously in their chosen career paths and lives.

i feel a strong connection to this character and her spirit, and this is partly due to her strength of character, because i feel like alot of the opportunities i have today are because of strong woman like her. this film also comes at a poignant time for woman as we unite and stand together as a collective voice for injustices such as #equalpay and the #metoo movement to name just a couple.

we live with so much social freedom with opportunities because of stories like these.
if you want to feel inspired. go see this movie.

anything can be a trigger...or anyone.
i was streaming today and an old friend came to watch. this old friend was honestly my favorite human and i loved him and i really miss him so much - but i saw his name and panicked.
i saw his name and thought of my rapist's voice and my mood immediately changed.
i saw his name and thought of my rapist's face and almost cried.
i saw his name and thought, oh my god i miss him but i can't let him back into my life because of all the memories he brings up. 
my rapist didn't just ruin san diego for me. he ruined friendships, my already fragile mental health, my self-esteem, and my confidence in who i think i am.

i miss you, my dude (you know who you are). and i really do want to talk to you and converse about life and your cats. i miss so many of our old mutual friends.

i know you won't believe me when i tell you what i went through, so i won't say anything...except that i miss you and i hope you're happy.

rape affects you so much beyond the initial violation. it affects your mind, your body, your emotional health, your relationships with everyone around you. and i will go on every day hoping to one day forget. i'll never forgive, but i can at least hope to be at peace.

thank you for reading.

text:
i went to the the vagina monologues this year for the first time. it was such an amazing show. 👌🏼
i particularly love how this show shares real stories of women from all walks of life. the stories shared range from funny to heartbreaking. 
this year a performer shared her story of assault and another shared her story of being a female in the prison system. 
i highly recommend everyone go watch it at least once (and it’s a fun date night idea, there were a lot of couples there 😉) and is great to raise awareness for the many things women face. 💁🏻‍♀️
if you’re in athens, all the proceeds from the show go to #projectsafe - a non profit whose mission is to end domestic violence. 
also my girl @mumbstheword is in the show and she is amazing. 💅🏾
the show is at the uga chapel tonight and tomorrow at 8pm!  #tvm #thevaginamonologues2018 #exploreathensga #athensga #uga #womenshealth #enddomesticviolence #metoo

nebraska republican sen. ben sasse introduced the born-alive abortion survivors protection act (s. 130) to protect babies who have survived failed abortions. sasse went to the floor of the senate monday to ask his colleagues to pass the bill by unanimous consent, but democrats objected. referencing the recent firestorm created by the virginia bill known as the repeal act, introduced by democrat delegate kathy tran and supported by democrat gov. ralph northam, sasse said: “this place fancies itself the world’s greatest deliberative body, but we would be deceiving ourselves if we ignored the biggest debate that’s been happening in america over the last 36 hours. a public elected official — the governor of one of the 50 states — has been defending a practice that is morally repugnant. the governor of virginia has been defending a practice that is repugnant to civilized people across the entire world.” “senate democrats had the chance today to prove they are not the party of infanticide, and instead they doubled down on extremism,” said susan b. anthony list (sba list) president marjorie dannenfelser after democrats blocked the bill. “the democratic party’s agenda of abortion on demand through birth and even beyond is radically out of step with the standards of decency the overwhelming majority of americans expect from their leaders.” “we urge the senate to bring the bill to the floor for a recorded vote so americans can know where each senator stands, and we urge its passage,” dannenfelser added. “it’s time to get this bill swiftly to the president’s desk for his signature.” ・・🦅🦅🦅🇺🇸🔴⚪️🔵🇺🇸🦅🦅#iglifethrupics #metoo #maga #sheepnomore  #abortion #chooselife #dayofmourning #savethebabies repost @christianandnerdy2.0
・・・

text: i was sexually abused from the age of 8 years old to 14 by a family member and sadly it’s more common then people think. i did speak up and he sadly only went to jail for a year or so which is bullshit. now that i have children of my own you better believe i will do everything in my power to protect them.  generations of sexual abuse will stop with me. i know that i can’t control everything that happens in my kids life but i know that i can control the fact that they will be safe with me and will be able to tell me everything. listen to your kids and talk to them often. it may be an uncomfortable conversation to have with them - but  teaching them early can save their lives. it can be the deciding factor of them fighting silently alone for years like me without knowing they have someone that will believe them verse feeling safe and knowing that they can speak up. we gain our  power back by education and speaking about our own experiences. if you are being abused or a survivior tell someone or talk to a counselor, family, and or friends. you are not alone and it is not your fault . you did not ask for it and the person that did that to you is sick. let us heal by letting go of the shame , guilt and pain. that burden was never meant for you to carry!

text:
let's talk my instagram evolution. got on instagram before tagged ig or insta.  now 2000+ followers makes me in ig terms a super lame and definitely not an influencer. really?

we evolved; always kept core.  at first i posted alot of travel pics, and random art (poetry, journalistic and digital visual art of mine). mostly, tho it was my favorite thing at time, being sex educator and lots of sex relationship articles. images created for advertising.  a few selfies, counseling around the world, global sex-ed seminars. my loyal followers are from those years.

life changed. perspective changed. everyone and their momma with video cam became overnight sex educator. not the psychological kind, the con kind. the smut kind. don't get me wrong. sex work and sex workers are fine, but this wasn't them, it was just some lames cashing in on the next trend. no knowledge base, no education, minimal experiential knowledge. main reason i called it quits. done with bs and wanna be's.

mental health wellness took presedence as profession and peer. purpose peer support™ once a campaign, became a service. [current ig]. today my focus is on mental health recovery and wellness. changed page 2017 to reflect. took all old pics down. then 2019 reintegrated psychosexual ed w/ concentration sex trauma/ipv, sex trafficking. i have credentials, degrees and life experience to bring to table.

brings me to point. now when i see hords of people/scams. jumping on the mental health wellness trend, including celebrities. to cash in. i'm insulted and concerned for our health, recovery and wellness.

i've said in posts before. stop listening to ill-informed, uneducated, unqualified. those who do not know or have background in psychology or mental health. do not have your interest at heart. always on next big scheme.

ask for credentials, state certification, college degree, recommendations. an ig page & pop up web doesn't mean you're professional. claim non profit or llc - prove it! read content on their page. so, you have mental illness - what diagnosis?

i may not be ig influencer. i'm an inspirer.my recovery real. this is a calling. my content real. i appreciate my followers. thank you.

welcome to the loud space, named after all those people who said you’re “too loud” simply because you voiced your thoughts. we are geared to discussing, with positive and respectful insight the following: #lgbtq+ lifestyle, #fashion, #trends, #health, #poc issues, #community, #heritage, #women and more.

instagram is a rapid growing community with many niches, sometimes we don’t fit to any niche in particular. that does not mean we cannot be part of a bigger picture. the loud space is meant to engage on hot topics and strike important discussions relating to #trending issues and news.

the loud space is a latino/lgbtq+ based project in new york, ny. join a multi-awareness environment that pushes the envelope in a body and mind #positive way. let’s think out loud together and #motivate our inner “loud” to create a better #world.

#popefrancis on tuesday publicly acknowledged the scandal of priests and bishops sexually abusing nuns and vowed to do more to fight the problem, the latest sign that there is no end in sight to the #catholicchurch’s abuse crisis — and that it now has a reckoning from the #metoo movement.

francis admitted to the problem for the first time in public during a news conference while returning to #rome from the #unitedarabemirates. the acknowledgment comes just two weeks before he hosts an unprecedented gathering of bishops to craft a global response to the scandal of priestly predators who target children and the superiors who covered up the crimes.

francis was asked about priests who target adult women — the religious sisters who are the backbone of the catholic church’s education, health care and social service ministries around the globe — and whether the holy see might consider a similar universal approach to combat that issue. “it’s not that everyone does this, but there have been priests and bishops who have,” francis told reporters. “and i think that it’s continuing because it’s not like once you realize it that it stops. it continues. and for some time we’ve been working on it.” “should we do something more? yes. is there the will? yes. but it’s a path that we have already begun,” francis said.

the issue has come to the fore amid the catholic church’s overall reckoning with the #sexualabuse of minors and the #metoo-inspired acknowledgement that adults can be victims of abuse whenever there is an imbalance of power in a relationship. in the past year, the associated press and other media have reported on cases of abused nuns in #india , #africa, #europe and #southamerica — evidence that the problem is by no means limited to a certain geographic area.

in november, the organization representing all the world’s female catholic religious orders, the international union of superiors general, publicly denounced the “culture of silence and secrecy” that prevented nuns from speaking out and urged sisters to report abuse to their superiors and police... 🖐🏾more in comments👇🏾#pedogate #pizzagate #spiritcooking

text:
gentle reminder...it’s okay if you felt good yesterday and feel uneasy today. 
it’s okay if last week you felt great, triumphant, present, easy-breezy week.  yet, this week sucks. 
it’s okay if you woke up today and felt hopeful about your day but now you’re ready for no pants and a nap. 
it’s okay if something had blown you off track.

don’t give up.  try giving in instead.  this is recovery and recovery has a way of dangling good days or good months in front of us only to change its course and dangle opportunities in front of us. 
the good days did happen.  log that!  they happened! 
when we feel good and alive is proof we can feel it again. 
even if today is hard.  even if tomorrow is hard too.

this is your reminder to sit in this. take extra care of yourself.  hang on until you feel strong again. because you will. ❤️

text:
•• h e a l i n g •• through the arts of survivors and allies #advocate #idaho ———————————————————————— as part of sexual assault awareness month, the family crisis center is seeking creative projects for the april 2019 “ healing – through the arts of survivors and allies”
the goal of this exhibit is three-gold:
1. create a space in which victims and survivors can feel validated in their experiences and can find hope in healing
2. give allies a platform through which to show their support for victims and survivors
3. increase awareness and empathy within our community for victims and survivors
we want to hear about any original work that will contribute to the message of the exhibit. photographers, painters, sculptors, choreographers, writers, graphic designers, curators – all creative disciplines are encouraged to apply.
entries close on friday, march 29. for anyone wishing to submit their piece, please contact julie at juliel@familycrisiscenter.info with “april 2019 exhibit” as the subject.

text:
•• s a n a c i ó n •• a través de las artes de sobrevivientes y aliados  #defensores #idaho ——————————————————————— como parte del mes de la concientización  de la agresión sexual el family crisis center está buscando proyectos creativos para la exhibición “sanación – a travéz de las artes de sobrevivientes y aliados.”
el objetivo es esta exposición es triple:
1. crear un espacio en el cual victimas y sobrevivientes puedan sentirse validados en sus experiencias y puedan encontrar esperanza 
2. proporcionar a los aliados una plataforma a través de la cual mostrar su apoyo a las victimas y sobrevivientes 
3. aumentar la conciencia y la empatía dentro de la comunidad para las victimas y sobrevivientes 
queremos saber sobre cualquier trabajo original que contribuya al mensaje de la exhibición. fotógrafos, pintores, escultores, coreógrafos, escritores, diseñadores gráficos – todas las disciplinas creativas son alentados a participar.
la aplicación para el evento cierra el viernes 29 de marzo. para cualquier persona que desee participar, comuníquese con julie al correo juliel@familycrisiscenter.info con “exhibición de abril 2019” en el tema del correo electrónico.

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
you champion other people
you encourage and love and even correct
you are the first to congratulate friends
and yet- there’s that voice
the things you would never say to anyone else
and green juice and yoga and supplements keep the voice at bay. 
mostly. 
who’s your champion?
having someone on your side cheering and clapping and wobbling for you until you can cheer and clap and wobble and celebrate yourself. 
that critical voice? 
it actually fades. 
having someone believe in you more than you believe in yourself changes the thinking. and then- watch out 🔥
won’t that be awesome 😉

text:
getting ready to buy this book. using brightly colored graphics, it goes over the some basics of feminism and talks about some of the core, popular feminist issues, such as the #metoo movement, the gender pay gap, intersectionality, equality in education, and even notable women such as malala yousafzi and frida kahlo. also, roxanne gay is a phenomenal writter and speaker, so i know this book is going to be good! it definitely seems great for those who want an introduction to feminism and need a good place to start. i'm already a feminist (although womanist fits me a bit better) but it never hurts to go back to basics and refresh youself some of the inportant points of it.

text:
"i am at ease
in my mind,
in my skin.
i have healed.
you did not win."
~kimmy
**********
as a reluctant player in the #metoo movement i've experienced tremendous highs and lows in the healing process.  for a while i was scared of everything and everyone.  now, two and a half years down the road i'm well on the path of healing.  my testimony, my truth helped get a predator off the streets. 
but still, i was left with the question of how do i get my groove back? how do i go back to feeling that my body is mine? how do i feel sexy again? 
this is my body of proof.  this boudoir photo shoot helped me do just that.  i'm not broken, i'm not ruined.  i am beautiful, i am strong. and i'm back.

text:
two law enforcement sources with knowledge of the investigation told cnn that chicago police believe jussie smollett paid two men to orchestrate the assault.
the brothers, who were arrested wednesday, were released without charges friday after chicago police cited the discovery of "new evidence." the sources told cnn that the two men are now cooperating fully with law enforcement.
smollett told authorities he was attacked early january 29 by two men who were "yelling out racial and homophobic slurs." he said one attacker put a rope around his neck and poured an unknown chemical substance on him. the sources told cnn that there are records that show the two brothers purchased the rope found around smollett's neck at an ace hardware store in chicago.

text:
february 16, 2018 is a date forever etched into my mind.

one year ago, my world was shaken, big time.  i was scared for my life.  i was drugged.  you never think that it will happen to you until it does. 
i’m not looking for sympathy.  i’m not going to write a novel on here and share all the details.  i just want others to know that they’re not alone and that we can get through this, together. #surivorloveletter#rapesurvivor#metoo#yourenotalone

text:
salah satu mitos yang sering kita dengar mengenai kekerasan seksual adalah bahwa pelaku adalah orang asing. sayangnya, menurut catatan tahunan komnas perempuan di tahun 2018, dari 350.000 kasus terlapor 80% terjadi di ranah publik dimana pelaku mayoritas adalah orang terdekat. korban enggan melapor karena diliputi banyak rasa bersalah, tidak bisa melawan, ditekan oleh keluarga karena "aib". sehingga sering kali pelaku bebas begitu saja. ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual tidak untuk merusak ketahanan keluarga, tapi memastikan bahwa anak - anak kita aman dari predator yang berada dalam keluarga kita sendiri. .
.
.
baca cerita lengkapnya di bit.ly/adikayah dan pastikan kamu tekan tombol "saya mendukungmu" / "i've got your back" untuk menunjukan dukunganmu kepada korban. #sahkanruupenghapusanks #lawanpelecehan #webelievevictims #stoppelecehan #metoo #beranibersuara  #mulaibicara

text:
‘embodied reckonings: “comfort women,” performance, and transpacific redress’ ~ one of those books i genuinely wish i’d written.
.
.
.
elizabeth son brilliantly explores and documents the power of theatre and performance as protest, and the very real opportunities for political and social change it presents. .
.
.
when people ask about my research, i am constantly reminded of the blaring gaps in our collective memory, specifically regarding women in history. since the early 90s surviving “comfort women” and their supporters have been protesting every wednesday in seoul to demand meaningful change and redress. it is the longest running protest in the world, yet in australia, in the uk, the term “comfort women” is largely met with blank stares.
.
.
.
this book is such a brilliant testament to the way women have sought, and continue to seek visibility in the face of historical erasure. .
.
.

text:
not my kid, not my school, not my problem is not the right message!  we need to come together as parents to protect our students. 
a title ix investigation found a male student at @fishers_highschool guilty of sexual harassment of several female students.  as punishment he was kicked off the swim team for the remainder of the season and has been suspended for the past 10 weeks.  on tuesday, the victim's parents were alerted that he was being reinstated on the swim team in order for him to compete in sectionals. 
@hseschools and @ihsaa1 are sending a clear message that it is acceptable to sexually harass, sexually assault, or threaten sexual assault if you are a star athlete.

text:
who are you? 
i seem to ask myself this all the time 
are you my fitness trainer 
or are you the coincidence i met twice in the line of the drug store?
are you the author of my favorite book?
or are you the singer with those cheesy melodies?
ok, no seriously, who are you?
do you start off as my best friend?
or does our  love begin as a forbidden story as those times from before? 
i want to know who you are. 
i’m searching all over for you, hoping i find you at the end of the road with a bouquet of my favorite kind of flowers in your hand. 
is it too late or am i too early? 
all these unanswered questions keep me up at night. 
my prince, or princess charming. one day, one day
please, don’t be late. - soul mate 
illustration by the talented @maniacodamore ❤️
.

text:
#playfulmemory, a little ditty all about provocation by creeper harassers who won't take no for an answer, has arrived to haunt your dreams.

this song is part klaus nomi, part julie andrews, lots of "the warriors" and a little david letterman and marilyn manson. it's even a little "possession" by sarah mclachlan plus "careless memories" by duran duran, sprinkled with the theme from "halloween" and the "say say oh playmate" hand-clapping playground chant.
.
.

zoenda mcintosh: lyrics, music, samples, 
synth piano, bass and drums

lee wiggins: sitar samples, farfisa, percussion,
electric guitar, echo piano, mix
.
.
audio available at peril.bandcamp.com
.

video posted on youtube in link above is "hold me while i'm naked" by george kuchar.
may the kuchar estate please monetize this video for any nickels that might come our way.

lyrics///
.
do you like to get people upset?
is that part of what fuels you?
wait a couple seconds
just do what i tell you
c’mon
i sit in the dark
with the doors all locked and freeze frame 
you were such a tease, hesitation blocked
and you said my name
so sometime admit
you want be with me
so some might call it
a playful memory
such a playful memory
come out to play

i like to provoke people 
so they think
c’mon
c’mon

i’m impatient and 
your “no” makes everything hard
just look what i do, when i’m without you
always saying your name
so say you’re nothing
if you are without me
say you’re nothing but
a playful memory
just a playful memory
come out to play
so they think
c’mon
play
.
.

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
how bout some good news?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
did you know that on thur feb 14th the child victim act was passed in new york?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
now victims of childhood sexual violence can file a civil suit until age 55, and for victims whose statute of limitations time has already run there is an opportunity to file suit for a one year period of time. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
additionally, the law extends the criminal statute of limitations by five years, allowing a prosecution for child sex abuse to be initiated before the victim turns 28 years old.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

how bout some good news?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
did you know that on thur feb 14th the child victim act was passed in new york?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
now victims of childhood sexual violence can file a civil suit until age 55, and for victims whose statute of limitations time has already run there is an opportunity to file suit for a one year period of time. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
additionally, the law extends the criminal statute of limitations by five years, allowing a prosecution for child sex abuse to be initiated before the victim turns 28 years old.

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."
dailyhunt

-

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
anyone carrying on the valentines day spirit with a rom com movie marathon this weekend? here are some diffuser blends to go with your fave! 💕because i said so: 4 drops peace & calming + 4 drops tangerine
💕the notebook: 4 drops idaho blue spruce + 2 drops geranium + 2 drops grapefruit
💕when harry met sally: 4 drops northern lights black spruce + 3 drops bergamot
💕gone with the wind: 4 drops patchouli + 3 drops bergamot
💕pretty woman: 4 drops ylang ylang + 2 drops idaho blue spruce + 2 drops orange
💕valentine’s day: 4 drops stress away + 2 drops peppermint
💕dirty dancing: 3 drops cedarwood + 3 drops lavender

what is your favorite rom com movie of all time?!

text:
paul chek @paul.chek is the man! -
#1 in the world for #sportsrehab #strengthtraining #holistichealth #holisticnutrition #modernshamanism #urbanshaman #healthguru #spiritualguru -
-
paul has successfully rehabbed more medically retired athletes to the to the multimillion dollar careers than anyone on the face of the planet. @dannyway from a broken neck in 1994, ryan hughes, gary roberts and @robbiemaddison just to name a few. he also pioneered the movement we see in all the gyms today on core function and swiss ball exerciseswhich is also directly related to the gut microbiome… his wife @pentheacrozier went to cambridge university and studied anthropological bio chemistry that was also used in figuring out the paleolithic mentalities around human diet.
-
-
his work on “working out“ versus “working in“ is groundbreaking in the field of exercise. with chronic elevated stress hormones like cortisol dominating the life of your average human through real and or perceived threats via the financial institutions or “terrorism” many people find themselves facing burn out and strenuous exercise will only add to that. understanding basic principles of tai chi or chi gong helps to get athletes back in the game that have been injured. including myself!
-
-

after studying and applying his systems for the past seven years as well as interviewing 25 of his top instructors i know this to be true not as opinion but honest fact. no other teacher on the face of the planet encompasses all aspects of our humanity. prove me wrong! -
-
most healthy people are not fit, most fit people are not healthy, and most spiritual teachers are not fit or healthy. imho
-
-
#paulchek #chekinstitute #correctiveexercise #metabolictyping #taichi #workingin #swissball  #swissballtraining @chekinstitute

text:
“men can’t be victims of assault by women,” is a comment that society as a whole has placed as a stigma on men. the myth that men can't be victims of sexual assault or assault by women is wrong. in fact, according to aasas (association of alberta sexual assault services), most research suggests that 10 to 20 percent of all males will experience some form of sexual abuse or sexual assault at some point in their lives. due to this stigma, men do not feel comfortable coming forward, because of the fear of judgment. the thought of a man being sexually assaulted by a woman is ignored or "ridiculous," some may say. we cannot pretend to have all the answers, but one thing that we all can improve is to listen and support.
···

text:
on wednesday, february 13th, the state legislature held its first hearing on sexual harassment in the workplace in 27 years. *
last year, the department of labor issued a draft model sexual harassment policy for all employers to adopt for their workplace. but, as my questioning showed, the did it with only 14 days of public input during "the doldrums of summer." *
if the #metoo movement has taught us anything, its that no matter how noble our intentions, we need to listen more to the experiences and stories of survivors and those who are affected by harassment.
——————
#harassmentfreealbany #harassmentfreeny #sexualharassment 
#newyorkstatesenate

text:
~chiron in aries~ i've been feeling this huge transit rolling through for the past month & monday, february 18th, it will finally be here until 2027. chiron did dip into aries for a couple months last year to give us a taste of things to come. chiron comes to heal wounds. aries says, "i am", and is about ego/self/identity. we'll be addressing issues related to our #selfworth, questions about who we are, why we're here, & our purpose. in the #us, we've always been known as a "nation of immigrants" but last year the uscis changed its mission & removed that promise. it's interesting to me that this week #trump declared a "national emergency" to deal with the "crisis at the border". our country, built on stolen land on the backs of slaves, is undergoing an identity crisis.
we'll also be doing intense work to heal the #divinemasculine. facing issues around the #patriarchy, #toxicmasculinity, #anger, #violence, & #sexualtrauma. last year we saw the rise of the #metoo & #timesup movement. there were school walkouts & marches against #gunviolence. expect that work to continue. aries was a lover & loyal, devoted, & protective father. he was in love with aphrodite, the goddess of love, & they had multiple children, including cupid/eros & harmonia. over the past several decades, #singlemothers & #deadbeatdads have become commonplace. we'll be healing those issues, as well. by the end of this cycle, we'll have gone from the #woundedwarrior to #nolimitsoldier. for me personally, the timing of working on the @this_is_jane_doc
couldn't be better! ready? come monday, roll up your sleeves ~ there's a lot of work to be done over the next 8 years! 
#chironinaries #astrology #immigration #fatherhood #lovers
